The best dish was a veal cheek goulash, served with orzo and a green harissa topping; full-flavoured meat, well-spiced with paprika. Other dishes were lacklustre. Under-grilled fennel let down one offering; a heaped plate of lentils was too monotonous in another — Guy Dimond";s:10:"post_title";s:9:"Jago Food";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:4:"jago";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2016-12-02 23:42:50";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2016-12-02 23:42:50";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:77:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=128";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"1";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:7;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:118;s:11:"post_author";s:2:"29";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-09-23 17:20:03";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-09-23 17:20:03";s:12:"post_content";s:456:"‘A place to share simple and honest food’? Well, Paesan at Exmouth Market sure don’t let on that there is something very extraordinary about them. Serving you true Italian peasant dishes, lovingly prepared and created, and in a most inspiring place.\r\n\r\nPaesan were nominated for Restaurant &amp; Bar Awards as well as shortlisted for menu of the year, doing it all with the simple yet magic formula of aperitivo, small plates, pasta, carne and pesce.";s:10:"post_title";s:6:"Paesan";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:6:"paesan";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2016-12-03 00:14:40";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2016-12-03 00:14:40";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:77:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=118";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"1";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:8;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:833;s:11:"post_author";s:2:"29";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-09-07 16:03:58";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-09-07 16:03:58";s:12:"post_content";s:748:"An idyllic Hyde Park-inspired tea parlour, hot chocolate and champagne bar, The Knightsbridge Lounge at The Park Tower Knightsbridge is the perfect destination for a spot of afternoon tea. Served under a canopy of elegant magnolia blossoms, the ambience is influenced by its distinguished location in between the cobbled street of Knightsbridge and the Royal gardens of Hyde Park.\n\nAn utterly relaxing and elegant retreat in the heart of Knightsbridge, here you can steep in the experience all afternoon - and into the evening too. At dusk, the luminous chandeliers are dimmed for an intimate glass of champagne.\n\nHere, you can drift into a different world and expect service with an emphasis on good old-fashioned hospitality with a modern touch.";s:10:"post_title";s:24:"The Knightsbridge Lounge";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:24:"the-knightsbridge-lounge";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-09-07 16:03:58";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-09-07 16:03:58";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=833";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"1";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}i:9;O:7:"WP_Post":24:{s:2:"ID";i:999;s:11:"post_author";s:2:"29";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-08-13 09:37:51";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-08-13 09:37:51";s:12:"post_content";s:859:"Although marooned in an industrial estate in Hackney Wick, The Counter is well worth a trip from far afield for its sturdy New Zealand breakfasts, perfect coffee and laidback atmosphere. Siblings Tom and Jess are the double act behind the venture. Growing up in Auckland, the pair were initially appalled by the lack of good coffee in London when they made it across the pond. Not wanting to leave us in caffeine poverty (kind souls) they took it upon themselves to set up The Counter in creative haven Hackney Wick.\n\nWhether you’re after a croissant (£2ish), baguette with bacon and avocado (£4ish) or the full monty (around a tenner), The Counter has something for everyone. They’ve also branched out into pies, but it’s the breakfasts that keep us repeatedly traipsing across London.\n\nhttp://twentysomethinglondon.com/the-counter-cafe-hackney-wick/";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Counter Café";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"counter-cafe";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-08-13 09:37:51";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-08-13 09:37:51";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:76:"https://pixelgrade.com/demos/listable-stock/?post_type=job_listing&amp;p=999";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:11:"job_listing";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}}s:10:"post_count";i:10;s:12:"current_post";i:-1;s:11:"in_the_loop";b:0;s:4:"post";r:136;s:13:"comment_count";i:0;s:15:"current_comment";i:-1;s:11:"found_posts";s:2:"30";s:13:"max_num_pages";d:3;s:21:"max_num_comment_pages";i:0;s:9:"is_single";b:0;s:10:"is_preview";b:0;s:7:"is_page";b:0;s:10:"is_archive";b:1;s:7:"is_date";b:0;s:7:"is_year";b:0;s:8:"is_month";b:0;s:6:"is_day";b:0;s:7:"is_time";b:0;s:9:"is_author";b:0;s:11:"is_category";b:0;s:6:"is_tag";b:0;s:6:"